The paper deals with the problem of distributed caching in wireless small cell networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The use of mean field games to solve the caching problem involves modeling the behavior of a large number of agents, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves stochastic differential games, which is a topic related to control theory and optimization (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper deals with the efficient use of storage space, which is a topic related to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
